section.section:
The board shall issue a probationary license to practice barbering to any person who:
Is at least seventeen and one-half (17-1/2) years of age;
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Has graduated from high school or possesses a General Educational Development (GED) certificate or transcript from an issuing institution that is recognized by the educational authority in the state from which the diploma, certificate, or transcript is issued;
Has graduated from a licensed school of barbering;
Has satisfactorily passed the probationary examination prescribed by the barber board, which shall include a practical assessment of the applicant's skills, including but not limited to a haircut and a chemical application; and
Has paid a fee not to exceed fifty dollars ($50).

text.section:
The board shall:
Issue a license to operate a barber shop to any barber licensed under the provisions of this chapter upon application and payment of a fee not to exceed fifty dollars ($50);
Refuse to issue the license upon a failure of the licensed barber to comply with the provisions of this chapter or the administrative regulations promulgated by the board;
Allow the licensed owner of a barber shop, which is licensed under this chapter, to rent or lease space in his or her barber shop to an independent contract owner; and
Allow an unlicensed owner of a barber shop, which is licensed under this chapter and managed by a barber licensed under this chapter, to rent or lease space in his or her barber shop to an independent contract owner.

The board shall issue a license to teach barbering to any person who:
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Has graduated from high school, or possesses a General Educational Development (GED) certificate;
Has been a licensed and practicing barber for at least eighteen (18) months;
Has satisfactorily passed the examination prescribed by the board by promulgation of administrative regulations; and
Has paid a fee not to exceed one hundred dollars ($100).

The board shall issue a license to any barber who holds an independent contract owner's license who:
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Has graduated from high school, or possesses a General Educational Development (GED) certificate;
Is a licensed and practicing barber under this chapter; and
Has paid a fee not to exceed fifty dollars ($50).

The annual renewal license fee for each type of license renewal shall be as follows:
Barber -- not to exceed fifty dollars ($50);
Teacher of barbering -- not to exceed fifty dollars ($50);
Barber shop -- not to exceed fifty dollars ($50);
Barber school -- not to exceed one hundred fifty dollars ($150); and
Independent contract owner -- not to exceed fifty dollars ($50).

section.section:
The fee per year for the renewal of an expired license, if the period of expiration does not exceed five (5) years, shall be as follows:
Barber -- not to exceed twenty-five dollars ($25) plus lapse fees;
Barber shop -- not to exceed twenty-five dollars ($25) plus lapse fees;
Barber school -- not to exceed twenty-five dollars ($25) plus lapse fees;
Teacher of barbering -- not to exceed twenty-five dollars ($25) plus lapse fees; and
Independent contract owner - - not to exceed twenty-five dollars ($25) plus lapse fees.
